typed-settings
--------------
Retrieve your application settings in a typed way, simply defining an interface.

Example:

// = Define the type of your settings.
public interface AppSettings {
    @javax.annotation.Named("config.settings.string")
    String getString();
}

// = Define the source and converters.
final SettingsBuilder builder = SettingsBuilder.create();
builder.addConfiguration(new PropertiesConfiguration(...));
builder.withConverter(Converters.dateConverter("dd.MM.yyyy"));

// = Build it.
final Settings settings = builder.build();
final AppSettings applicationSettings = settings.getSettings(AppSettings.class);

// = Use it.
applicationSettings.getString()